{
  "stem": "15028.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And with my father's help, and-- to create, build back a house for my grandfather and uncle in Bosha.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, well, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there was, number one-- I mean, as far as the religion in-- in our life, my father, my grandfather, my mother, my-- my father-- number one, my father took me to mikveh every Monday and Thursday, when I was a child.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Friday, that was the big day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was mikveh.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a steam-- a big steam room in the town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And especially, as we didn't have showers, and we didn't have water in the-- it felt pretty good, as a child, if I look back, to go into a hot mikveh in the wintertime.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was going, not only in the wintertime, even the summertime, in the steam rooms-- one big steam room.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then-- then they had Fridays.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They could have brought a leu or two leu.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They brought, with a barrel, water, into the top.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they poured the hot water and they-- and if-- if some people took a second to use the same water, what somebody else used, it was good enough for them, paid only half a leu and use the same water to bathe, to wash up before Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that-- the mik, no question about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "On [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Shabbos was a very important event in the town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Number one, we made-- we had a bakery.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we had-- we made cholent.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's a famous dish, by-- the Jewish orthodox, or non-orthodox, or orthodox people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the cholent was taken into the bakery, to the baker, a top.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that way would be some meat, and so on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Somehow, I always wondered how come they didn't mix up.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
